            "body": "Reproduction for python with lsp server `pylsp`:\r\n\r\n1. install pylsp\r\n2. nvim config:\r\n```vim\r\ncall plug#begin(stdpath('data') . '/pylsp_plugged')\r\nPlug 'neovim/nvim-lspconfig'\r\ncall plug#end()\r\n\r\nlua <<END\r\nlocal lsp = require('lspconfig')\r\nlsp.pylsp.setup { settings = { pylsp = { plugins = { pylint = { enabled = true }}}}}\r\nEND\r\n```\r\n3. Press `o` in second line in a python file with this content (there is a diagnostic from pycodestyle on the last line):\r\n```py\r\n\"\"\" This file actually has a docstring \"\"\"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nNUMBER = 100\r\n```",
